Side-to-side stepping helps improve lateral movement and balance, strengthening the muscles in the hips and legs. 

• Stand with your feet hip-width apart.
• Step to the right with your right foot, then bring your left foot to meet your right foot.
• Repeat this step, moving to the right for several steps.
• Then step to the left with your left foot, bringing your right foot to meet your left.
• Continue for several steps in each direction.
